      "text": "**Emacs**, Vim is a race car, Emacs is your RV, you load it with stuff after stuff, it already comes with more stuff than you require. Lets get few things straight, Emacs is slow, the lisp code compiles forever even in modern computers, it is not editor at all, there is no difference between Emacs or Eclipse or any other massive applications. But like how Javascript or NodeJS now became ubiquitous and everywhere, even though JS as language thrown under the bus all the time, Emacs in spite of poor performance allows you to do anything you imagine, it is called kitchen sink, there is modern browser to everything else in between text editor. Emacs has this nice keyboard chaining concept, you don't have to keep pressing your mod keys you start with one but after which you simply tap keys based on command chains, for e.g. you press C-x then simply press 5 to starts window commands, now pressing 0 will close current frame or press 2 to create new frame. Everything in emacs, thousands of things available as function in M-x mode. Emacs could become Vim, Vim could never become Emacs, should tell you everything about its extensibility."
